ZCZC GE98
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 292300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING A BROAD AREA OF LOW PRESSURE WILL BE CENTRED SCANDINAVIA
WITH A TROUGH EXTENDING SW THROUGH THE N SEA AND MOV SE. HIGH PRESSURE
WILL ALSO BE SITUATED W OF IRELAND EXTENDING S TO THE AZORES AND N TOWARDS
ICELAND. THROUGH TUESDAY THE HIGH PRESSURE RIDGES E ACROSS THE UK AND TOWARDS
GERMANY WITH THE MAIN HIGH CENTRE GRADUALLY MIGRATING INTO IRELAND DURING
WEDNESDAY. AT THE SAME TIME SHALLOW LOW CENTRES WILL MOV NE IN THE ATLANTIC
TOWARDS ICELAND AND AROUND THE TOP OF THE HIGH. SHALLOW LOW PRESSURE WILL
ALSO DEVELOP OVER IBERIA BEFORE DRIFTING N AND W TOWARDS THE BAY OF BISCAY.
NEAR GALES ARE LIKELY MONDAY EVENING AND TUESDAY THROUGH THE NEERN PART OF
CULLERCOATS PERHAPS GALE FORCE FOR A TIME IN S UTSIRE AND FISHER BEFORE
GRADUALLY EASING INTO WEDNESDAY. NON HAZARDOUS WINDS ARE THEN EXP IN CULLERCOATS
